  "The Earth system is composed of four major spheres: the atmosphere (air), hydrosphere (water), geosphere (land/rock), and biosphere (life). These spheres continuously interact and exchange energy and matter.": "",
  "Which Earth sphere includes all living organisms?": "",
  "Hydrosphere": "",
  "Geosphere": "",
  "Biosphere": "",
  "Atmosphere": "",
  "The biosphere encompasses all living organisms on Earth, from deep-sea microbes to high-altitude birds. It spans parts of the atmosphere, hydrosphere, and geosphere wherever life exists.": "",
