  "An open system": "",
  "A completely isolated system": "",
  "A dynamic system with unlimited matter exchange": "",
  "A closed system (exchanges energy but not significant matter)": "",
  "Earth is essentially a closed system for matter, meaning very little matter enters or leaves, but it freely exchanges energy (receiving solar radiation and emitting infrared radiation into space).": "",
  "Which sphere includes all water on Earth?": "",
  "The hydrosphere includes all water on Earth in all forms -- oceans, rivers, lakes, glaciers, groundwater, and even atmospheric water vapor. Approximately 97% is saltwater in the oceans.": "",
